==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nonexistence
<hw>Non`ex*ist"ence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The state of not existing; absence of existence; the negation of
being; -- usually used with reference to existence in the real world, or
logical possibility; <as>as, the <ex>nonexistence</ex> of vaporware does
not go unnoticed long</as>.</def> <rj><au>A. Baxter.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> nonentity{1}.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A thing that has no existence.</def> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nonexistent</ent>⟦br⟧
